'Hail, [placeholder].

'We met with no resistance on our journey, and I believe I have you to thank for that.

Talk to Éowyn
'My people are safe, [placeholder]. Let us return to them.'
Éowyn, Mágla, and Ellen Fremedon have made their preparations, and now, they stand ready to guard the people of Kingstead as they travel to Dunharrow.
'Are you ready to venture into the Dimholt, [placeholder]?'
A pale figure stands in the distance...
Éowyn can be found on the Firienfeld at Dunharrow.\n\nYou have arrived at Dunharrow, and now Éowyn wishes to speak with you.

Talk to Éowyn at Dunharrow
Ur can be found outside the Dark Door.\n\nYou have cornered the Orc and should now defeat it.
Walk with Éowyn
The Orc stands waiting outside the Dark Door
Éowyn can be found outside the Dark Door in the Dimholt.\n\nYou have defeated the Orc-leader and brought peace to the people of Kingstead.

'The Orcs are vanquished, and my people are safe. Those Orcs knew not the warriors they faced! 

'Dunharrow shall once again be a haven for the people of Rohan, and my people will remain free of the Enemy's grip.

'Let us not tarry long here, [placeholder], for this place fills me with dread.'
